<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11123f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11123f">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11123f"> 123(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Louis Philippe / Il a laiss&eacute; le moment conspirer / il n&apos;a conspir&eacute; lui m&ecirc;me que / par ses d&eacute;sirs dont il est / probable qu&apos;il avait peur</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">D&apos;apr&egrave;s le caract&egrave;re de Louis-Philippe, on doit pr&eacute;sumer qu&apos;il ne prit aucune r&eacute;solution, et que sa timidit&eacute; politique, se renfermant dans sa fausset&eacute;, attendit l&apos;&eacute;v&eacute;nemen comme l&apos;araign&eacute;e attend le moucheron que se prendra dans sa toile. <mark>Il a laiss&eacute; le moment conspirer; il n&apos;a conspir&eacute; lui-m&ecirc;me que par ses d&eacute;sirs, dont il est probable qu&apos;il avait peur</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Louis-Philippe: In keeping with the character of Louis-Philippe, it must be presumed that he never took a decision, and that his political timidity, wrapping itself in his duplicity, awaited the outcome as the spider awaits the gnat that will be caught in his web. He left conspiracy to the moment; he himself conspired only in his wishes, which he probably feared.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> [<mark>Louis-Philippe</mark>] 148</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
